0.title: Rules
0.body:
Flash Point: Fire Rescue
a cooperative game by Kevin Lanzing
-------------------------------------------

Rules PDF:
www.indieboardsandcards.com/fpfrenglishrules.php

Use the buttons to automate some of the tedius between turn tasks.  See button tab for details.

The AI does NOT handle hotspots, detect when fire causes a hazmat to explode, or detect when a victim/POI is destroyed by fire.  Watch for these events and resolve them manually.

Victims placed in the saved or lost spaces on the left will update the scoreboard on the right.

If all 24 cubes are placed, the building will collapse and fire will rain down.

1.title: Buttons
1.body:
[b][u]Buttons[/u][/b]:
[b]Roll[/b] - Roll the dice.  Pushing the button is not needed to update the board state, it's just provided as a convenience.  The dice can be manipulated however you like.

[b]Update[/b] - Usually smoke will detect if it next to fire.  If for some reason it doesn't, update will re-evaluate all the smoke.

[b]Advance fire[/b] - At the end of every turn, roll the dice then click the advance fire button to lay down smoke, turn smoke into fire, or create an explosion on a space with fire. 

[b]Drop POI[/b] - If there are less than 3 POIs on the board, roll the dice and click the drop POI button.

[b]Setup game[/b] - Click this button to lay down all the doors, three initial explosions, and three hazmats.  This button will then disapear

function unpack()
    boardName=boardParams['boardName']
    blackPositions=boardParams['blackPositions']
    redPositions=boardParams['redPositions']
    sliderYPosition=boardParams['sliderYPosition']
    yPosition=boardParams['yPosition']
    poiPath=boardParams['poiPath']
    vWalls=boardParams['vWalls']
    hWalls=boardParams['hWalls']
    radius=boardParams['radius']
    boardPosition=boardParams['boardPosition']
--    boardGUID=boardParams['boardGUID']
    doorXOff=boardParams['doorXOff']
    doorZOff=boardParams['doorZOff']
    hotspots=boardParams['hotspots']
    testvar=""
    testTable={}
    print("board set to " .. boardName)
--    print("dz set to ", doorZOff)
end


function onload()
    unpack()
    redDie = getObjectFromGUID(redDieGUID)
    blackDie = getObjectFromGUID(blackDieGUID)
    board1 = getObjectFromGUID(board1GUID)
    redSlider = getObjectFromGUID(redSliderGUID)
    blackSlider = getObjectFromGUID(blackSliderGUID)
    smokeBag = getObjectFromGUID(smokeBagGUID)
    poiBag = getObjectFromGUID(poiBagGUID)
    poiBag.shuffle()
    hotspotBag = getObjectFromGUID(hotspotBagGUID)
    hazmatBag = getObjectFromGUID(hazmatBagGUID)
    doorBag = getObjectFromGUID(doorBagGUID)
    doorBagLoc = doorBag.getPosition()
    doorBagLoc = {doorBagLoc.x,doorBagLoc.y+5,doorBagLoc.z}
    boardBag = getObjectFromGUID(boardBagGUID)
    boardBagLoc = boardBag.getPosition()
    boardBagLoc = {boardBagLoc.x,boardBagLoc.y+5,boardBagLoc.z}
    cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID(cubeBagGUID)
    savedZone = getObjectFromGUID(savedZoneGUID)
    injuredZone = getObjectFromGUID(injuredZoneGUID)
    houseZone = getObjectFromGUID(houseZoneGUID)
    oldRed=redDie.getValue()
    oldBlack=blackDie.getValue()
    menuBoard=getObjectFromGUID(menuBoardGUID)
end

function useRanch()
    getBoard(RanchHouseGUID)
end

function useBeach()
    getBoard(BeachHouseGUID)
end

function useBrownstone()
    getBoard(BrownstoneGUID)
end

function useHighRise()

function getBoard(newboardGUID)
--print ("bg=" .. boardGUID)
    boardGUID=newboardGUID
    menuBoard.destruct()
    local params = {}
    params.position = boardPosition
    params.guid=boardGUID
    params.rotation = {0,180,0}
    params.callback = "configureBoard"
    params.callback_owner = Global
    board=boardBag.takeObject(params)
end

function configureBoard()
    boardParams=board.getTable("newBoardParams")
--print("it=",boardParams["doorZOff"])
    unpack()
    board.setPosition(boardPosition)
    board.lock()
    boardGUID=board.getGUID()
end

function setupBoard ()
--print("boardGUID=",boardGUID)
    local params= {}
    params.rotation = {0,0,0} -- no rotation for any of these things
    if setupPhase ==0 then -- dropping doors`
        for i,hotspotLoc in pairs(hotspots) do
            params.position=hotspotLoc
            hotspot=hotspotBag.takeObject(params)
            hotspot.setPosition(params.position)
        end
        for col=1,9 do -- each column of the vertical walls
            for row=1,6 do-- each cell of the vertical walls
                if vWalls[col][row]== 3 then
                    doorX=blackPositions[col]-radius
--print("Dz=",doorZOff)
                    doorZ=redPositions[row]+doorZOff
                    dropDoor(doorX,doorZ)
                end
            end
        end
        for row=1,7 do -- each column of the vertical walls
            for col=1,8 do-- each cell of the vertical walls
                if hWalls[row][col]==3 then
                    doorX=blackPositions[col]+doorXOff
                    doorZ=redPositions[row]+radius
                    dropDoor(doorX,doorZ)
                end
            end
        end
        updateFlag=1
    end
    if setupPhase == 1 or setupPhase==3 or setupPhase==5 then -- rolling for new Explosion
        if setupPhase == 1 then -- the first time, just roll
            if boardGUID==HighRiseGUID then
                red=math.random(6)
                black=2
            else
                red=math.random(3,4)
                black=math.random(3,6)
            end
--red=5
--black=6
            redDie.setValue(red)
            blackDie.setValue(black)
            print ('first roll set to ',black,',',red)
        elseif setupPhase==5 then -- do the flip black and reroll red thing for third explosion
--print("entering 5")
            if boardGUID==HighRiseGUID then
                black=math.random(8)
                red=5
                redDie.setValue(red)
                blackDie.setValue(black)
--print("hirise")
            else
--print("not hirise")
                black=black+4
                if black>8 then -- flip the black die
                    black=black-8
                end
                blackDie.setValue(black)
                count = 0
                spaceFree=0
                while spaceFree==0 and count<40 do
                    red=math.random(6)
                    redDie.setValue(red)
                    if map[red][black]==nil then
                        spaceFree=1
                    end
                    count=count+1
                end
            end
            print ('third roll set to ',black,',',red)
        else -- the second time, roll but reroll if there is already fire
            if boardGUID==HighRiseGUID then
                red=math.random(6)
                black=7
                redDie.setValue(red)
                blackDie.setValue(black)
            else
                count = 0
                spaceFree=0
                while spaceFree==0 and count<40 do
                    silentRoll()
                    if map[red][black]==nil then
                        spaceFree=1
                    end
                    count=count+1
                end
            end
            print ('second roll set to ',black,',',red)
        end
        hotspotX=blackPositions[black]+(radius/2)+0.2
        hotspotZ=redPositions[red]+(radius/2)+0.2
        params.position={hotspotX,yPosition+0,hotspotZ}
        hotspot=hotspotBag.takeObject(params)
        hotspot.setPosition(params.position)
    end
    if setupPhase > 0 and setupPhase <7then
        exploded=advanceFire(1)
        if (setupPhase==3 or setupPhase==5) and (exploded==1) then
            setupPhase=setupPhase+1 -- jump forward if there was an immediate explosion
        end
--print('setup=', setupPhase)
    end
    if setupPhase >6 then
        count=0 -- used to prevent infinate loops
        hazmatDropped=0
        getMap()
        while hazmatDropped==0 and count<40 do
            silentRoll()
            if map[red][black]==nil then
                params.position = {blackPositions[black],yPosition-0.5,redPositions[red]}
                lastObject=hazmatBag.takeObject(params)
                lastObject.setPosition(params.position)
                map[red][black]=lastObject
                hazmatDropped=1
                updateFlag=1
--                print ("dropped hazmat in phase ",setupPhase)
            end
            count=count+1
            if count>30 then
                print ("reroll count is getting high ",count)
            end
        end
    end
    setupPhase=setupPhase+1
--setupPhase=0 -- debugging, abort after doors dropped
    if setupPhase>9 then
        setupPhase=0
    end
end

function dropDoor(doorX,doorZ)
    local params = {}
    params.position = {doorX,yPosition-0.5,doorZ}
    params.rotation = {0,180,180}
    lastObject=doorBag.takeObject(params)
    lastObject.setPosition(params.position)
end

function silentRoll()
    red=math.random(6)
    black=math.random(8)
    redDie.setValue(red)
    blackDie.setValue(black)
end

function rollDice()
    redDie.roll()
    blackDie.roll()
end

function setSliders (red,black)
--    print("black=",black," red=",red," ypos=",yPosition)
    local params = {}
    params.blackposition = {blackPositions[black],sliderYPosition,boardParams.zEdge}
    blackSlider.setPosition(params.blackposition)
    params.redposition = {boardParams.xEdge,sliderYPosition,redPositions[red]}
    redSlider.setPosition(params.redposition)
end

function getRow(thing)
    local newRow=1
    local thingPos=thing.getPosition()
    local thingZ=thingPos.z
    for i=1,6 do
        if thingZ<redPositions[i]+radius then
            newRow=i
        end
    end
--    print("found row ",newRow)
    return newRow
end

function getCol(thing)
    local newCol=1
    local thingPos=thing.getPosition()
    local thingX=thingPos.x
    for i=1,8 do
        if thingX>blackPositions[i]-radius then
            newCol=i
        end
    end
--    print("found col ",newCol)
    return newCol
end

function checkPOI()
--    print("checkPOI called!")
    local params = {}
    lastPOI=getObjectFromGUID(lastPOIGuid)
    if isFlipped(lastPOI)==1 then
        return 1-- don't do it for revealed pois
    end
    lastPOIrow=getRow(lastPOI)
    lastPOIcol=getCol(lastPOI)
    --[[
    if newPOIrow~=lastPOIrow or newPOIcol~=lastPOIcol then -- skip a frame
        lastPOIrow=newPOIrow
        lastPOIcol=newPOIcol
    else
    --]]
        nd=poiPath[lastPOIrow][lastPOIcol] -- new direction
--        print("direction ",lastPOIcol,"-",lastPOIrow,"=",nd)
        newPOIrow=lastPOIrow
        newPOIcol=lastPOIcol
        if nd==1 or nd==2 or nd==8 then
            newPOIrow=lastPOIrow-1
        end
        if nd==2 or nd==3 or nd==4 then
            newPOIcol=lastPOIcol+1
        end
        if nd==4 or nd==5 or nd==6 then
            newPOIrow=lastPOIrow+1
        end
        if nd==6 or nd==7 or nd==8 then
            newPOIcol=lastPOIcol-1
        end
--        print("new ",newPOIcol,"-",newPOIrow)
        params.position = {blackPositions[newPOIcol],yPosition+2,redPositions[newPOIrow]}
        params.rotation = {0,0,0}
    --    params.callback = "setScript"
    --    lastPOI=poiBag.takeObject(params)
        lastPOI.setPositionSmooth(params.position)
        lastPOI.setRotationSmooth(params.rotation)
--    end
end

function setPOIScript() -- called by routine to take from bag
    poiScript = [[
  function onCollisionEnter(collision_info)
    on=collision_info.collision_object
    onLocation=on.getPosition()
    myLocation=self.getPosition()
    if onLocation.y > myLocation.y then -- skip if this isn't the top
        return 1
    end
    onName=on.getName()
    if onName=="POI" or onName=="Fire fighter" or onName=="Fire" then
        print("POI landed on ",onName,", moving to next space.")
        callLuaFunctionInOtherScript(Global,"checkPOI")
    end
    myGUID=self.getGUID()
--    print("myGUID=",myGUID)
    Global.setVar("lastPOIGuid",myGUID)
end    ]]
--    print("g=",lastPOIGuid)
    thisPOI=getObjectFromGUID(lastPOIGuid)
--    print(thisPOI.getName())
--    print(poiScript)
    thisPOI.setLuaScript(poiScript)
--    print()
end

function pullPOI()
--    print(poiScript)
    local params = {}
    params.position = {blackPositions[black]+POIoffset,yPosition+2,redPositions[red]+POIoffset}
    params.rotation = {0,0,0}
    params.callback = "setPOIScript"
    params.callback_owner = Global
    poiList=poiBag.getObjects()
    params.guid = poiList[1]["guid"]
    lastPOIGuid=params.guid
--    print(params.guid)
    params.params = {params.guid}
--    print("guid=",params.guid)
    lastPOI=poiBag.takeObject(params)
    lastPOI.setPosition(params.position)
    lastPOIcol=black
    lastPOIrow=red
    newPOIcol=black
    newPOIrow=red
    POIcount=POIcount+1
--    lastPOI.setLuaScript(poiScript)
--    dropPOI(lastPOI,black,red)
end

function dropFire(type,col,row) -- type 1 =fire
--    print("col=",col," row=",row," ypos=",yPosition)
    local params = {}
    params.position = {blackPositions[col],yPosition+1.5,redPositions[row]}
    if type==1 then
--      params.flipped=true
        params.rotation = {0,0,0}
    else
        params.rotation = {0,0,180}
--      params.flipped=false
    end
    if col < 9 then
--        print(table.concat(params.position," "))
        newThing=smokeBag.takeObject(params)
        newThing.setPosition(params.position)
        newThing.setRotationSmooth(params.rotation,false,true)
        lastObject=newThing
        updateFlag=1
        table.insert(fireList,newThing)
--        map[row,col]=newThing
    end
end

function isFlipped(thing)
    rot=thing.getRotation()
--    print("  ",rot.z)
    if rot.z>150 and rot.z<240 then
        return 1
    else
        return 0
    end
end

function advanceFire(fireState)
    exploded=0 -- keep track of whether there was an explosion
    if fireState~=1 then -- make sure firestate is 0 or 1
        fireState=0
    end
    getMap()
--    print("checking ",red,"-",black)
    if map[red][black]==nil then
--        print("blank found")
        dropFire(fireState,black,red) -- plop down new smoke
    else
        thing=map[red][black]
--        rot=thing.getRotation()
--        if rot.z>150 and rot.z<240 then
        if isFlipped(thing)==1 then
--            print("smoke found")
            thing.flip()
            lastObject=thing
            updateFlag=1
        else
--            print("Explosion!")
            doExplosion()
            exploded=1
        end
    end
    scanSmoke()-- change any smoke next to fire into fire
    return exploded
end

function doExplosion()
    map[red][black].addForce({0,3,0})
    for direction=1,4 do -- 1=n,2=e,3=s,4=w
        checkDirection(direction,black,red)
    end
end

function checkDirection(vector,col,row)
    ncol=col -- default for north or south
    nrow=row -- default for east or west
    if vector==1 then -- checking northward
        nrow=row-1
    elseif vector==3 then --south
        nrow=row+1
    elseif vector==2 then -- east
        ncol=col+1
    else -- west
        ncol=col-1
    end
    wc=checkWall(vector,col,row)
--    print("vc=",vector," wc=",wc)
    if wc ==0 then -- made it through the wall
        if ncol<1 or ncol>9 or nrow<1 or nrow>6 then -- off the edge
            return
        elseif map[nrow][ncol]==nil then
--            print("blank found")
            dropFire(1,ncol,nrow)
            return
        else
            map[nrow][ncol].addForce({0,3,0})
            checkDirection(vector,ncol,nrow)
        end
    end
end

function checkWall(direction,col,row,nondestructive) -- nondestructive optional
    orientation="h" -- default norizontal for north or south
    wcol=col -- default column for north, south, or west
    wrow=row -- default row for north, east, or west
    if direction==1 then -- north
--        cell=hWalls[row][col]
        -- do nothing, defaults are fine
    elseif direction==2 then -- east
        wcol=col+1
        orientation="v"
    elseif direction==3 then -- south
        wrow=row+1
    else -- west
--        cell=vWalls[col][row]
        orientation="v"
    end
    if orientation=="h" then
        cell=hWalls[wrow][wcol]
        cellX=blackPositions[wcol]
        cellZ=redPositions[wrow]+radius
    else
        cell=vWalls[wcol][wrow]
        cellX=blackPositions[wcol]-radius
        cellZ=redPositions[wrow]
--        print("VCELL=",cell)
    end
--print("d",direction,"-",orientation," r",wrow,"c",wcol,"=",cell)
    if cell==0 then -- open wall
        return 0
    elseif cell>2 then -- a doorway
--        checkDoor() -- should look a list of doors using cellX and cellZ
--        print("door-",cell)
        if cell==3 then -- a door space with no door
            return 0
        else
            door=doorList[cell-3]
            doorState=isFlipped(door)
            if nondestructive==nil then
                door.setPosition(doorBagLoc)
                if orientation=="h" then
                    hWalls[wrow][wcol]=3
                else
                    vWalls[wcol][wrow]=3
                end
            end
            return doorState -- 1 if door is closed, 0 if open
--[[            if rot.z>150 and rot.z<240 then -- closed door, stop
                return 1
            else -- open door, keep going
                return 0
            end
            --]]
        end
    elseif cell==-1 then -- an unbreakable wall
        return 1
    else -- 1 or 2, wall with HP
        --add routine to check cube damaged list
        wallDamage=0
        for i,thing in pairs(cubeList) do
            position=thing.getPosition()
            x=position.x
            z=position.z
            if checkRadius(x,z,cellX,cellZ)==1 then
                wallDamage=wallDamage+1
            end
        end
        if nondestructive==nil and wallDamage<cell then
            local params = {}
    --        placeCube()
    --        print("wall damaged")
            if orientation=="h" then
--                hWalls[wrow][wcol]=cell-1 -- remove after cube checking is added
                params.position = {cellX - 0.3 + wallDamage*0.6,yPosition,cellZ}
            else
--                vWalls[wcol][wrow]=cell-1 -- remove after cube checking is added
                params.position = {cellX,yPosition,cellZ + 0.2 - wallDamage*0.6}
    --            print("  setting vwalls[",wcol,"][",wrow,"] to ",cell-1)
            end
--            print(table.concat(params.position," "))
            if cubeBag.getQuantity()>0 then
                newThing=cubeBag.takeObject(params)
                newThing.setPosition(params.position)
                lastObject=newThing
                updateFlag=1
            end
        end
--        print("solid wall")
        if (wallDamage>=cell) then -- 2 cubes
            return 0
        else
            return 1
        end
    end
end

function checkRadius(x,z,xMid,zMid) -- check to see if x and z are inside the radius of a circle around xMid and zMid
    aradius=radius-0.4 -- adjusted radius
    xMin=xMid-aradius
    xMax=xMid+aradius
    zMin=zMid-aradius
    zMax=zMid+aradius
    if x>xMin and x<xMax and z>zMin and z<zMax then
        return 1
    else
        return 0
    end
end

function killPOI(POI)
    printToAll("A Point Of Interest was engulfed in flames.", {1,1,1})
    startZ = deadZ -- the place to put dead POIs
    startX = deadX
    poiGUID=POI.getGUID()
    positionCounter=injured
    resultString="A victim was lost!"
    resultColor={1,0,0}
    for i,guid in pairs (falseAlarmLIST) do
        if guid==poiGUID then
            startZ=deadFAZ -- it's a false alarm, so start farther back
            positionCounter=i
            resultString="Fortunately, it was a false alarm!"
            resultColor={0,1,0}
        end
    end
    dropX=startX+(deadXoff*(positionCounter%2))
    dropZ=startZ+(deadZoff*math.floor((positionCounter)/2))
    local params = {}
    params.position = {dropX,yPosition,dropZ}
    params.rotation = {0,0,180}
    POI.setPosition(params.position)
    POI.setRotation(params.rotation)
    printToAll(resultString, resultColor)
end

function getMap() -- get information about the board state
    getFire()
    map = {}
    noteList = {}
    radius=boardParams['radius']
    for row=1,6 do
        map[row] = {}
        for col=1,8 do
            xMid=boardParams['blackPositions'][col]
            zMid=boardParams['redPositions'][row]
            cell="0"
            for i,fireToken in pairs(fireList) do
                position=fireToken.getPosition()
                x=position.x
                z=position.z
                if checkRadius(x,z,xMid,zMid)==1 then
                    map[row][col]=fireToken
                    cell="X"
--                    print("rotvalue=",fireToken.getRotationValue())
                    if isFlipped(fireToken) == 1 then
                        cell="S"
--                        print("smoke because ",rot.z)
                    end
                end
            end
            for i,thing in pairs(endangeredList) do
                position=thing.getPosition()
                x=position.x
                z=position.z
                if checkRadius(x,z,xMid,zMid)==1 then
                    if cell=="X" then -- if this position has a POI and fire
                        killPOI(thing)
                    end
                end
            end
            for i,thing in pairs(doorList) do
                position=thing.getPosition()
                x=position.x
                z=position.z
                -- remove after door checking is changed to use objects
                if checkRadius(x+radius,z,xMid,zMid)==1 and col>1 then
--                if x+radius>xMin and x+radius<xMax and z>zMin and z<zMax and col>1 then -- check to the left for a door
                    if vWalls[col][row] > 2 then -- only if this could have a door then
                        vWalls[col][row]=i+3 -- 3 = door space with no door, 3+=door index
--                        print("setting VWall[",col,"][",row,"]=",i+3)
                    end
                end
                if checkRadius(x,z-radius,xMid,zMid)==1 and row>1 then
--                if x>xMin and x<xMax and z-radius>zMin and z-radius<zMax and row>1 then -- check to the top for a door
                    if hWalls[row][col] > 2 then -- only if this could have a door then
                        hWalls[row][col]=i+3 -- 3 = door space with no door, 3+=door index
--                        print("setting HWall[",row,"][",col,"]=",i+3)
                    end
                end
            end
            -- add section for damage cubes.  Create "damaged" list with co-ords
            table.insert(noteList,cell)
        end
        table.insert(noteList,"\n")
    end
--    setNotes(table.concat(noteList))
    updateScoreboard()
end

function getFire() -- and doors, and cubes, and POIs.  Poorly named function
    noteList = {}
    fireList = {} -- reset the list of fire tokens
    doorList = {} -- and the doors
    cubeList = {} --    and the cubes
    endangeredList = {} -- and the cubes
    damage=0
    POIcount=0
    allObjects=getAllObjects()
--    allObjects=houseZone.getObjects()
    for i,thing in pairs(allObjects) do

        if thingName=="Fire" then
            table.insert(fireList,thing)
--            table.insert(noteList,thing.getName())
        elseif thingName=="Door" then
            table.insert(doorList,thing)
--            print("found door")
        elseif thingName=="Damage" then

        elseif thingName=="POI" then
            POIcount=POIcount+1
--print ("POIc=" .. POIcount)
        end
    end

--    spark=fireList[1]

--    print("fire gotten")

function getCell(row,col) -- 0 = empty, 1= smoke, 2= fire
    if row<1 or row>6 or col<1 or col>8 then
        return 0 -- out of bounds
    elseif map[row][col]==nil then
        return 0 -- empty cell
    else
        local thing = map[row][col]
        if isFlipped(thing)==1 then
--            print("found smoke at ",row,col)
            return 1 -- it's smoke
        else
--            print("found fire at ",row,col)
            return 2 -- it's fire
        end
    end
end

function checkSmoke(row,col)
    contents=getCell(row,col)
--    print(row,col,"-",contents)
    if contents==1 then
--        north=checkWall(1,col,row,1)
--        print("north=",north)
        north=checkWall(1,col,row,1)==0 and getCell(row-1,col) or 0
        east=checkWall(2,col,row,1)==0 and getCell(row,col+1) or 0
        south=checkWall(3,col,row,1)==0 and getCell(row+1,col) or 0
        west=checkWall(4,col,row,1)==0 and getCell(row,col-1) or 0
        if north==2 or east==2 or south==2 or west==2 then
            thing=map[row][col]
--            thing.flip() -- replace with function to instantly flip
            thing.setRotation({0,0,0})
            return 1 -- flashed over
        else
            return 0
        end
    else
        return 0 -- didn't flash
    end
end

function scanSmoke()
--    print("testvar=",testvar)
    getMap()
    clear=0
    i=0 -- used to prevent infinate loops
    while clear==0 do
--        print("beginning")
        clear=1 -- assume we are going to make it through
        for row=1,6 do
            for col=1,8 do
                flashed=checkSmoke(row,col)
                if flashed==1 then -- it was smoke and turned to fire
                    clear = 0 -- we didn't make it through
--                    print ("flashed at ",row,col," restarting ",i)
                end
            end
        end
        i=i+1
--        print("i=",i)
        if i>20 then
            clear =1 -- something is wrong, break out
        end
    end
end

function onObjectEnterScriptingZone(zone, enter_object)
    if enter_object.getName()=="POI" then -- only worry about POI counters
        if zone==savedZone then
            saved=saved+1
            savedVector=1
        elseif zone==injuredZone then
            injured=injured+1
            savedVector=-1
        end
        if zone==houseZone then
            --[[
            endangered=0
            houseList=houseZone.getObjects()
            for i,thing in pairs(houseList) do
                if thing.getName()=="POI" then
                    endangered=endangered+1
                end
            end
            --]]
            endangered=endangered+1
        else
            if enter_object.getGUID() == catGUID then
                catSaved=savedVector
            elseif enter_object.getGUID() == dogGUID then
                dogSaved=savedVector
            end
        end
        updateScoreboard()
--        print("zoneGUID=",zone.getGUID())
    end
end

function onObjectLeaveScriptingZone(zone, enter_object)
    if enter_object.getName()=="POI" then -- only worry about POI counters
        if zone==savedZone then
            saved=saved-1
        elseif zone==injuredZone then
            injured=injured-1
        end
        if zone==houseZone then
            endangered=endangered-1
            --[[
            endangered=0
            houseList=houseZone.getObjects()
            for i,thing in pairs(houseList) do
                if thing.getName()=="POI" then
                    endangered=endangered+1
                end
            end
            --]]
        else
            if enter_object.getGUID() == catGUID then
                catSaved=0
            elseif enter_object.getGUID() == dogGUID then
                dogSaved=0
            end
        end
        updateScoreboard()
    end
end

function updateScoreboard()
    --[[
    endangered=0
    houseList=houseZone.getObjects()
    for i,thing in pairs(houseList) do
        if thing.getName()=="POI" then
            endangered=endangered+1
        end
    end
    --]]
    if damage>23 then
        scoreboard="[ff0000][b][u]Building collapse![/u][/b][-]\n"
        rainFire()
    elseif injured>3 then
        scoreboard="[ff0000][b][u]Defeat![/u][/b][-]\n"
    elseif saved>9 then
        scoreboard="[00ff00][b][u]Perfect victory![/u][/b][-]\n"
    elseif saved>6 then
        scoreboard="[00ff00][b][u]Victory![/u][/b][-]\n"
    else
        scoreboard="[0000ff][u]Score[/u][-]\n"
    end
    scoreboard=scoreboard .. "Damage = " .. damage
    scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nSaved =" .. saved
    scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nLost =" .. injured
    if catSaved==1 then
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nThe cat has been saved!"
    end
    if dogSaved==1 then
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nThe dog has been saved!"
    end
    if dogSaved==1 and catSaved==1 then
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nPet victory!"
    end
    if catSaved==-1 then
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nThe cat has been lost!"
    end
    if dogSaved==-1 then
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nThe dog has been lost!"
    end
    if dogSaved==-1 and catSaved==-1 then
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nTragedy!"
    end
--print("endangered=" .. endangered .. " POI=" .. POIcount)
    if endangered<3 then
        if endangered==0 then
            scoreboard= scoreboard .. "\n\nThere are no POIs"
        elseif endangered==1 then
            scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\n\nThere is only one POI"
        else
            scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\n\nThere are only two POIs"
        end
        scoreboard=scoreboard .. " on the board."
        if POIcount < 18 then
            scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nDon't forget to roll for new ones."
        else
            scoreboard=scoreboard .. "\nBut the bag is empty. Almost done!"
        end
    end
    setNotes(scoreboard)
end

function rainFire()
--    spark=fireList[1] -- fire to copy from
    if fireRainCounter==0 then
        spark=getObjectFromGUID(sparkGUID)
        for row=1,6 do
            for col=1,8 do
                local params = {}
                sparkX=blackPositions[col]
                sparkZ=redPositions[row]
                sparkY=20+math.random(20)
--                print("sx=",sparkX," sy=",sparkY," sz=",sparkZ)
                params.position={sparkX,sparkY,sparkZ}
                this=spark.clone(params)
                this.unlock()
            end
        end
    end
    fireRainCounter=1
end

function update()
    red = redDie.getValue()
    black = blackDie.getValue()
    if oldRed != red or oldBlack != black then
        if redDie.resting and blackDie.resting then
            oldRed=red
            oldBlack=black
            setSliders(red,black)
        end
    end
    if updateFlag==1 and lastObject.resting==true then
        if restingCounter > 1 then
            scanSmoke()
            updateFlag=0
--            print("lastObject is a ",lastObject.getName(), " guid=",lastObject.getGUID())
--            print("updating phase",setupPhase)
            if setupPhase>0 then
                setupBoard()
            end
            restingCounter = 0
        else
            restingCounter=restingCounter+1
        end
    end
end

    location=self.getPosition()

function round(num, idp)
  return tonumber(string.format("%." .. (idp or 0) .. "f", num))
end

function onCollisionEnter(collision_info)
    -- body...
    on=collision_info.collision_object
    rot=on.getRotation()
    location=on.getPosition()
    print("on name=",on.getName()," GUID=",on.getGUID())

    print("x=",round(location.x,2)," y=",round(location.y,2)," z=",round(location.z,2))
--    on.setName('Fire')
end
